          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The beryllium oxide target was a ceramic sheet of",
                " thickness 178 mg/cm2 (for Egamma < 200 MeV) or",
                " 290 mg/cm2 (for Eg > 200 MeV)."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "MAGFR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " 900 MeV/C magnetic spectrometer."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "COIN",
                "MWDC",
                "SCIN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " drift chamber with delay-line readout",
                " which was triggered by a coincidence between three",
                " plastic scintillators. Each scintillator had an area",
                " 0.25 m x 0.75 m and thickness 12.5 mm and was coupled",
                " through a twisted-strip light guide to a 75 mm",
                " diameter EMI 9821B photomultiplier tube."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The (gamma,p) cross sections leading to the 15N ground",
                " and first three excited states were extracted by",
                " fitting the measured photoproton energy spectra with",
                " a calculated spectrum containing the (unknown) cross",
                " sections and the (known) bremsstrahlung spectrum."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                " Cross section obtained from the fits of measured",
                "  photoproton energy spectra were corrected for dead",
                "  time losses."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "DATA-ERR",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The errors quoted are the statistical",
                " uncertainties combined with an energy-dependent",
                " error which varies from 1.7% for Egamma < 151 MeV to",
                " 9% at Egamma = 380 MeV due to the uncertainty in the",
                " correction for nuclear interactions of the protons",
                " in the plastic scintillator and iron absorbers. In",
                " addition, there are systematic uncertainties:"
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-1",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " uncertainties in the incident photon flux"
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-2",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " uncertainties in the dead time correction"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The differential cross section for 16O(gamma,p)15N",
                " process has been measured in the energy range",
                " Egamma = 100 - 400 MeV at laboratory angles of 45,90,",
                " and 135 degree. The cross sections for the (gamma,p)",
                " reactions leaving 15N in its ground state, in its",
                " first and second excited states at E-EXC about 5.3",
                " MeV and in its third excited state at E-EXC = 6.3 MeV",
                " were extracted from the tip region of the proton",
                " spectra measured at a series of bremsstrahlung",
                " end-point energies. The data were compared with",
                " calculations based on a direct, single-particle",
                " knockout mechanism and on mechanisms involving two",
                " particles in the intermediate state."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "HISTORY": [
